<li id="cite_note-bridgett-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-bridgett_13-0" title="">^</a></b> "Effects of listening to Mozart and Bach on the performance of a mathematical test" <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFBridgettCuevas.2C_J.2009">Bridgett, D.J.; Cuevas, J. (2000). <i>Perceptual and Motor Skills, 90</i>. pp.&#160;1171–1175. ISBN.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Perceptual+and+Motor+Skills%2C+90&amp;rft.aulast=Bridgett&amp;rft.aufirst=D.J.&amp;rft.au=Bridgett%2C+D.J.&amp;rft.au=Cuevas%2C+J.&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B1171%E2%80%931175&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Mozart_effect"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news"><a href="http://www.nature.com/news/2007/070409/full/070409-13.html" class="external text" title="http://www.nature.com/news/2007/070409/full/070409-13.html" rel="nofollow">"Mozart doesn't make you clever"</a>. Nature.com<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.nature.com/news/2007/070409/full/070409-13.html" class="external free" title="http://www.nature.com/news/2007/070409/full/070409-13.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.nature.com/news/2007/070409/full/070409-13.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-04-03</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Mozart+doesn%27t+make+you+clever&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=Nature.com&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Fnews%2F2007%2F070409%2Ffull%2F070409-13.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Mozart_effect"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
